---
import MainHead from '../components/MainHead.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Title from '../components/Title.astro';
import Wrapper from '../components/Wrapper.astro';
import Subheading from '../components/Subheading.astro';

import { Markdown } from 'astro/components';

interface MarkdownFrontmatter {
  date: number;
}

const { title = 'About' } = Astro.props;
const { description = 'Designer and writer' } = Astro.props;

let essayPosts = await Astro.fetchContent('../pages/essays/*.md');
essayPosts = essayPosts.sort((a, b) =>  new Date(b.date).valueOf() - new Date(a.date).valueOf());


---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <MainHead
      title={'About'}
      description={description}
    />
    <style lang="scss">

      div {
        background: #141414;
        padding: 15px;
        margin: 0;
        border-radius: 10px;
      }
      dl {
        overflow: scroll;
        display: flex;
        gap: 40px;
        padding-left: 30px;
        dt, dd {
          padding: 0;
          margin: 0 !important;
          width: 400px;
        }
      }
      dt {
        color: white;
        font-size: 7em;
        font-family: var(--font-display);
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <Nav title={title} />
    <main>
      <Wrapper>
        <Title>About</Title>
        <Subheading>About this website</Subheading>
        <Markdown>
          This website was built with [Astro](https://astro.build) and published via [Netlify](https://netlify.com). You can view all the code [over on GitHub](https://github.com/robinrendle/robinrendle.com). Paragraphs are set in James Edmonson’s [Degular](https://ohnotype.co/fonts/degular) and titles are set in David Jonathan Ross and Bethany Heck’s ever-so-lovely [Job Clarendon](https://djr.com/job-clarendon).
        </Markdown>

        <Markdown>
          You can contact me via email: [robinjrendle@gmail.com](mailto:robinjrendle@gmail.com)
        </Markdown>
    </Wrapper>
      <Subheading>Timeline</Subheading>
      <dl>
        <div>
          <dt>1990</dt>
          <dd>Born. July. United Kingdom. England. Cornwall. Plymouth.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>1993</dt>
          <dd>My brother. My mom. A big house on a large plot of land. Games. Endless games. And singing and playing and dancing by the fire place. The floor is lava!</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>1997</dt>
          <dd>Driving. Endless rain. My brother in the backseat, giggling. Kinects. PlayStation. Reading books in hotel lobbies. Final Fantasy VII. Animorphs. Hotels. Hotels. Hotels. Enormous rooms full of strangers. So many strangers. My father. Speaking on stage...</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2007</dt>
          <dd>Trapped. Futureless. Bad grades. Bad friends. Drinking. Music. Atheism. Socialism. Feminism. Fraudsters. Con men. Grifters. Everywhere. Even from within our family.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2008</dt>
          <dd>Plymouth University. English Literature. Books. Books. Books.  CSS3. HTML5. Music. Bass. Drums. Garageband. Remixing. Sadness. Loneliness. Drinking.  Computers. Escape.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2010</dt>
          <dd>Novels. Graphic design. Book design. Web design. A footnote in a book. “The Department of...” Huh. Interesting. More reading. Typography! Letters! .woff and .ttf! The ampersand! Diacritics, baby!  An enormous door. A world. Unlocking. </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2011</dt>
          <dd>More footnotes. Each time the same: “Thanks to the <a href="https://www.reading.ac.uk/typography/">Department of Typography and Graphic Communication</a>.” A phone call. A train. Reading University. A walk across a marsh (lost on campus). The building. The door. An interview. That guy! Nerves. Another train home. Days. Weeks. An email. Accepted? Accepted! Life changing. A train. Lucky beyond comprehension. Smart, kind people. Surrounded. Not good enough. The feeling of the world being nudged back into place.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2012</dt>
          <dd>My father. His leg. The amputation. A vale of tears. The absolute wonder of the NHS. Indesign. Work. Work. Work. End of year show. A bathroom stall. Sick. Frightened. The future, outside. More trains. Nottingham. Interview. Erskine Design. Internship. The command line. Tinkering with Sass. Begging for a loan. For food. More tears. More sadness. Writing is relief.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2013</dt>
          <dd>No money. The first <a href="/notes/setting-up-a-default-type-stylesheet">blog post</a>. Lonely. Writing. Working. </dd>
        </div>

        <div>
          <dt>2014</dt>
          <dd>No Erskine. No clients. No money. A train. Plymouth. Tail firmly between legs. Freelancing. Fucking up. Fixing things. Building. Working. An email. <a href="https://css-tricks.com">CSS-Tricks</a>. Staff writer. Tiny heart. Bigger blog.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2015</dt>
          <dd>Trains. London. Round glasses. A drink. Dark rooms. A holiday. New York City. <a href="https://www.robinrendle.com/notes/with-teeth-of-metal-and-glass/">Teeth, metal, glass.</a> Heartbreak. Gym. Lessons. Gym. Motorcycle. Pride. Momentum. Gym. Absolute beef cake. A tweet. <a href="https://www.designerfund.com/">Designer Fund</a>. An email. An invitation. A train. A plane. San Francisco. BART. SOMA. An interview. Gusto. Money. Money. Money.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2016</dt>
          <dd>Papers. Documents. Passports. More documents. More waiting. Arguments. Screaming. A motorcycle (Billy). Driving up through the wind and rain. Wales. Alone. Family breaking apart. Blogging and crying. Plymouth again (briefly). My parents. An awkward drive. The airport. A handshake. A plane. San Francisco. Money. Restaurants. Dora. Jez. Brexit. Heartbreak. A protest in the castro. Overwhelming sadness. The little green light.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2018</dt>
          <dd>
            <a href="/notes/the-triumph-street-triple">The Triumph Street Triple</a> (Billy #2).


            notes/from-san-francisco-to-los-angeles
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2019</dt>
          <dd><a href="/notes/christmas-in-la">Christmas in LA</a>. Christmas. A book. A breakdown. Delete. Delete. Delete. <a href="essays/systems-mistakes-and-the-sea">Systems, Mistakes, and the Sea</a>.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2020</dt>
          <dd>Sentry.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>2021</dt>
          <dd>Pandemic. Lockdown. Friends leaving for Seattle, LA, New York. That’s it. No more toxic relationships. Working out. Being kind to myself. Hinge. Swiping. Endless swiping. An evening. A woman in my apartment. A joke. More jokes. Crying because of the jokes. Something else. Not funny. Serious. Sex. Love. Moving in together. A trip to Seattle. More jokes. Always jokes. Our first home.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
